  distinguishable across epochs.

### Attempt 2 (GREEN)
- Solution: Asset script uses manually-implemented Adam optimizer (no optax)
  for both normal [1,32,32,1] (1000 epochs, lr=0.01) and overfit
  [1,128,128,128,1] (5000 epochs, lr=0.005) networks.
- Trophy checkpoints saved at {0, 200, 500, 1000} epochs (not {0,10,100,1000})
  because Adam's convergence profile produces clearly-distinguishable fits at
  those milestones. The notebook text reflects this.
- Notebook training cell (PRETRAINED=False path) uses vanilla SGD (as per brief)
  for pedagogical transparency; PRETRAINED=True (default) loads Adam-trained
  checkpoints.
- Input normalisation x->[-1,1] added to prevent tanh saturation in first layer.

